<subSubSection id="ADC16551871A1C4FFF7E5E5EFBDBF866" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="E56436DA871A1C4FFF7E5E5EFEACF891" blockId="1.[151,1436,446,1836]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="D7AFEAC8871A1C4FFF7E5E5EFE8EF9F2" bold="true" box="[198,330,1589,1615]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Discussion</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis id="D7AFEAC8871A1C4FFEEA5E5EFEABF9F2" bold="true" box="[338,367,1589,1615]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="22DB4D59871A1C4FFED75E5DFDFFF9F2" authorityName="Gaglioti, Romaniuc &amp; A. K. Monro" authorityYear="2011" box="[367,571,1590,1615]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Urticaceae" genus="Pilea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis id="D7AFEAC8871A1C4FFED75E5DFDFFF9F2" box="[367,571,1590,1615]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Pilea brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the 
<emphasis id="D7AFEAC8871A1C4FFD535E5DFC92F9F2" box="[747,854,1590,1615]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Dentatae</emphasis>
-group of 
<bibRefCitation id="814A4B2B871A1C4FFC735E5DFB44F9ED" author="Weddell, H. A." box="[971,1152,1590,1616]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" pagination="104 - 163" refId="ref2210" refString="Weddell, H. A. (1869) Pilea. In: De Candolle, A. (ed.), Prodromus, systematis naturalis regni vegetabilis 16 (1). Paris. pp. 104 - 163." type="book chapter" year="1869">Weddell (1869)</bibRefCitation>
and the 
<emphasis id="D7AFEAC8871A1C4FFB5A5E5DFA83F9F2" box="[1250,1351,1590,1615]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Fallaces</emphasis>
- group of 
<bibRefCitation id="814A4B2B871A1C4FFF015E31FE98F9C9" author="Killip, E. P." box="[185,348,1626,1652]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" pagination="367 - 394" refId="ref1897" refString="Killip, E. P. (1936) New species of Pilea from the Andes. Contributions from the United States National Herbarium 26 (8): 367 - 394." type="journal article" year="1936">Killip (1936)</bibRefCitation>
. It represents the first record of the 
<emphasis id="D7AFEAC8871A1C4FFCAD5E30FCB9F9C9" box="[789,893,1627,1652]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Fallaces</emphasis>
-group in Brazil. It is characterised by being glabrous, with toothed pinnately veined leaves, petioles of up to 3 cm long and paniculate inflorescences. 
<taxonomicName id="22DB4D59871A1C4FFF2F5ECFFEA1F900" authorityName="Gaglioti, Romaniuc &amp; A. K. Monro" authorityYear="2011" box="[151,357,1700,1725]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Urticaceae" genus="Pilea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis id="D7AFEAC8871A1C4FFF2F5ECFFEA1F900" box="[151,357,1700,1725]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">Pilea brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="22DB4D59871A1C4FFDF05ECFFC7BF903" authority="Killip (1925: 296)" authorityName="Killip" authorityPageNumber="296" authorityYear="1925" box="[584,959,1700,1726]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Urticaceae" genus="Pilea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lippioides">
<emphasis id="D7AFEAC8871A1C4FFDF05ECFFD1FF900" box="[584,731,1700,1725]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="18">P. lippioides</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="814A4B2B871A1C4FFD5B5ECFFC7BF903" author="Killip, E. P." box="[739,959,1700,1726]" pageId="1" pageNumber="18" pagination="289 - 297" refId="ref1868" refString="Killip, E. P. (1925) New tropical American species of Urticaceae. Journal of the Washington Academy of Sciences 15: 289 - 297." type="journal article" year="1925">Killip (1925: 296)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which occurs in the eastern and central Cordillera of Colombia, at elevations between 2400 and 3000 m. The two species may be readily distinguished by leaf and petiole morphology, staminate inflorescence arrangement and achene size as summarized here:
</paragraph>
